# Phase 4 Implementation Plan — Mobile Experience & Core Pages

## Goals
1.  **Mobile Native Feel**: Implement a proper Bottom Navigation bar for mobile users, replacing the hidden sidebar.
2.  **Functional Library**: Build out the "History" and "Liked Videos" pages so sidebar links work.
3.  **User Personalization**: Create a robust **Settings** page for account and preference management.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Mobile Navigation ([components/BottomNav.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/components/BottomNav.tsx))
-   **New Component**: A fixed bottom bar visible only on mobile (hidden on desktop).
-   **Icons**: Home, Trending, Creator (+), Subscriptions, Library.
-   **Integration**: Update [Layout.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/components/Layout.tsx) to include this conditionally.

### 2. Core Library Pages
-   **History Page ([app/history/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/history/page.tsx))**:
    -   List view of recently watched videos.
    -   "Clear History" button.
-   **Liked Videos ([app/liked/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/liked/page.tsx))**:
    -   Grid view of liked content.
    -   Shuffle/Play All buttons.

### 3. Settings Page ([app/settings/page.tsx](file:///C:/GoLive/app/settings/page.tsx))
-   **Layout**: Sidebar navigation for settings (Account, Appearance, Notifications).
-   **Features**:
    -   Profile picture upload (mock).
    -   Theme toggle (if applicable, or just refined dark mode settings).
    -   Notification preferences.

## Verification
-   Resize browser to mobile width (<768px) to see Bottom Nav appear and Sidebar disappear.
-   Clicking "History" and "Liked Videos" in sidebar/nav works and shows content.
-   Settings page toggles feel responsive.
